        <V n="text" t="single">
          <T n="single">0x52B8580A<!--String: "I keep thinking about what you said; I'm turning it over in my mind a lot to see how it fits. Meanwhile, that Sim who rejected me actually told me they wanted to be friends and that they feel alone without me around.\n\nYou know, no matter what, I don't think I do want to be with them. I don't know yet if I want to try harder for a different life or if, well, maybe I should just keep my life the way it is now. Some Sims seem like they can change practically on a moment’s notice.\n\nI wonder if other Sims think about this sort of thing as much as I do? But everything’s complex. A lot of Sims will talk to me about how they think a lot of elements of nature are really simple and that Sims just complicate them, but they're wrong.\n\nAll over nature, there are all sorts of differences and variances. Our understanding of the world is expanded all the time, right? Maybe it’s all about my understanding of myself, not about change itself. Huh."--></T>
